comment0.text=\n\ The\ time\ interval\ (in\ milliseconds)\ between\ animation\ frames.\ Thus,\n\ for\ example,\ to\ draw\ a\ frame\ 20\ times\ per\ second,\ you\ would\ return\n\ 50.\ This\ method\ is\ called\ once\ at\ the\ beginning\ of\ the\ animation,\ so\n\ changing\ the\ value\ during\ the\ animation\ will\ have\ no\ effect.\n\ \n\ @return\ the\ time\ interval\ (in\ milliseconds)\ between\ calls\ to\ this\ class'\n\ "tick"\ method.\n
comment1.params=
comment1.target=java.awt.Dimension\ canvasSize()
comment1.text=\n\ The\ size\ of\ the\ canvas\ we\ are\ drawing\ our\ animation\ on.\n\ \n\ @return\ the\ size\ of\ the\ canvas,\ in\ pixels.\n
comment2.params=
comment2.target=java.awt.Color\ backgroundColor()
comment2.text=\n\ The\ background\ color\ with\ which\ to\ paint\ the\ canvas\ before\ the\ animation\n\ frame\ is\ drawn.\ \ This\ method\ is\ called\ at\ each\ tick,\ so\ the\ background\n\ color\ can\ change\ dynamically\ by\ having\ this\ method\ return\ different\ values.\n\ \n\ @return\ the\ desired\ background\ color\n
comment3.params=
